Well the poll results for SCP Anon were a tie. So I flipped a coin and landed on Cephalopods!

These humanoids developed from Octopi, Squids and Cuttlefish. The mantle has expanded downwards and fused with several tentacles to form limbs. The internal shell made of chitin has developed and extended into an endoskeleton made of a chitin and proteinaceous matrix that provides support while being very flexible.

Still being cephalopods, the nerve clusters around the head tentacles have atrophied while the clusters in the head and body have developed. Giving them a decentralized nervous system when combined with their regenerative properties the ability to survive serious head-wounds.

They have unique lungs which came about through their gills and mantle-opening. As a result they either breath in through the sides of their mouth, or on the sides of their head, and exhale through their siphon. Rather than taste or smell with their mouth, they do it with their tentacles. Which also includes their limbs.

In terms of genitals. The siphon has been repurposed. Serving as a cloaca of sorts. In males the hectocotlyus has been fused with the penis. Resulting in them having one less tentacle than females, and an odd number of face tentacles.

Females tend to be larger than males in mass, and are wide and thick. Partially due to the massive reproductive system they have, needing to lay big eggs. Males by comparison are much lankier and taller.
